gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Knicks 110, 76ers 96
gameRecap.excerpt: The Knicks snap a four-game losing streak as they defeat the 76ers, 110-96. Bojan Bogdanovic (8-13 FG, 6-6 3PT) led the Knicks with 22 points as Jalen Brunson (21 points and 12 assists) and Josh Hart (18 points, 12 rebounds, three assists) totaled 39 points in the win. Tyrese Maxey led the Sixers with 35 points, six rebounds, and five assists. The Knicks improve to 34-22 as Philadelphia moves to 32-23.
